TY  - JOUR
TI  - Stability and Speed of Adjustment under Retiming of Lags
AU  - Harriff, Richard
AU  - Donald V. T. Bear
AU  - Conlisk, John
AB  - [The subject is retiming of lags in a system of linear difference equations. The issues are (i) the effect of lag retiming on stability and (ii) the effect of lag retiming on speed of adjustment. Regarding (i), a theorem due to Bear [1] is sharpened; and new conditions for stability to survive under a retiming of lags are obtained. Regarding (ii), the main results concern the effects of "lag perturbations" and "spread perturbations" on speed of adjustment in models with nonnegative coefficients.]
C1  - Full publication date: Mar., 1980
